properties.Name: BankruptcyCreditor
properties.Description:
Creditor(s) specified for the associated Bankruptcy action.

One to whom the debtor owes money or who claims to be owed money by the debtor.

Columns.Name: BankruptcyProceedingId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Bankruptcy Proceeding.

Columns.Name: CreditorPartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.

Columns.Name: CreditorClaimAmount
Columns.Description: The amount that the credit claims is owed to them.

Columns.Name: SecuredCreditorIndicator
Columns.Description:
A secured creditor can claim a specific collateral for repayment of a debt.

The secured creditor can reclaim the collateral to sell.

Columns.Name: ProofOfClaimDescription
Columns.Description:
A Proof of Claim is filed in bankruptcy court by creditors.

The bankruptcy trustee has the power to determine if the proof of claim is valid.

Columns.Name: ProofOfClaimFiledDate
Columns.Description: The date that the proof of claim was filed.
